<h1>Case 8 — Smart Emergency Beacon System</h1>

<h2>Brief Description</h2>
<p>
The Smart Emergency Beacon System alerts citizens during emergencies by activating beacon lights, 
sirens, and public notification messages across Velora. 
It guides people toward safe zones using automated routing and fast signal propagation.
</p>

<h2>Rising Problems</h2>
<ul>
    <li>People often panic due to unclear guidance during emergencies.</li>
    <li>Manual broadcasting of alerts is slow and unreliable.</li>
    <li>Beacon failures disrupt coordinated evacuation.</li>
    <li>No real-time network to route citizens safely.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Solutions / Logic Used</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>BFS (Breadth-First Search):</strong> Spreads emergency signals through beacon nodes quickly.</li>
    <li><strong>Hash Tables:</strong> Stores beacon health, signal strength, and operational status.</li>
    <li><strong>Queue:</strong> Handles alert broadcast requests in order.</li>
    <li><strong>Graph Traversal:</strong> Identifies safest and nearest evacuation paths.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Suitable SDGs</h2>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 11 — Sustainable Cities & Communities</strong>
    <p>Improves emergency preparedness and reduces disaster impacts.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 9 — Industry, Innovation & Infrastructure</strong>
    <p>Uses smart interconnected beacon systems for rapid emergency response.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 3 — Good Health & Well-Being</strong>
    <p>Helps protect citizens during life-threatening situations by guiding them safely.</p>
</div>

